The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Self-defence plea in boy attack on teacher
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Self-defence plea in boy attack on teacher
          A STAFF REPORTER                          The Metro report on Tuesdays incident                                  
	The father of the Class IX student of St Aloysius Orphanage and Day School who had allegedly kicked and punched the principal on Tuesday has lodged a police complaint accusing the principal of nearly suffocating his son.        
	The railway employee lodged the general diary at Golabari police station in Howrah on Wednesday night.         
	According to the complaint, Father George Anthony had caught the 16-year-old by his throat, cutting off his air supply and forcing him to strike back in self-defence.         
	The school authorities have suspended the boy.        
	The schools managing committee will constitute a panel next week to probe the incident. The boy shall remain suspended till the managing committee makes a decision on the basis of the inquiry report, said a senior member of the panel.        
	The boy had kicked and punched Father George after he allegedly slapped him twice for changing his place in the middle of a concert.        
	We have received a complaint from the father of a student of St Aloysius Orphanage and Day School alleging that the principal had beaten up his son. The father admitted that his son had retaliated. We will soon start an investigation into the incident, said an officer of Golabari police station.                                                                                                                                                          
